This paper involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques to generate memes with captions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and machine learning techniques for language processing. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques to prepare the dataset, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses CV techniques to understand the visual content of memes, which makes cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) another possible sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques for training the model, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves artificial intelligence (AI) techniques for generating memes, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category.
